Three suspects have been arrested for allegedly attacking and robbing Chinese contractors of Ksh.6 million at Kariminu (II) Dam site in Gatundu North, Kiambu County. Police said investigations are still ongoing following the Friday night incident where two Chinese contractors were accosted. According to Kiambu County Police Commander Ali Nuno, the thugs who were armed with pistols could have gained entry through a tunnel used for water supply. The three suspects, who are being held at the Kamwangi Police Station, include the watchman at the site and the Chinese contractorsâ€™ driver. Video Of The Day: CAS Rachel Shebesh and athlete Asbel Kiprop share their mental health journeys